  "title": "M&E Project Coordinator/ M&E Engineer #77897",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Building and Construction/ Manufacturing (Furniture)</li><li>Position Title: <strong>M&E Project Coordinator/ M&E Engineer</strong></li><li>Working Location: Mandai Estate</li><li>Working Hours: 5 Days (Mon - Fri, 8.30am – 5.30pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic Salary + Variable Bonus + Medical & Dental Benefits</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Plan, coordinate, and oversee all mechanical and electrical (M&E) works on site</li><li>Review technical drawings and specifications, identifying discrepancies and reporting them to the Project Manager</li><li>Maintain and monitor all M&E-related documentation and records</li><li>Coordinate shop drawings and ensure alignment with project requirements</li><li>Supervise and manage M&E sub-contractors to ensure timely and accurate execution of work in accordance with contract drawings and specifications</li><li>Liaise with relevant authorities, clients, and sub-contractors on matters related to shop drawings, equipment submissions, inspections, testing, and commissioning</li><li>Organize and lead M&E coordination meetings to align all parties involved</li><li>Update and report on M&E progress, issues, and developments to the Project Manager</li><li>Collaborate effectively with site teams to ensure smooth workflow and project execution</li><li>Negotiate and seek approval for any M&E-related changes while ensuring compliance with local regulations and standards & other ad-hoc duties as assigned</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or higher qualification in Mechanical & Electrical Engineering, Building Services, or related field</li><li>Minimum 1 year of relevant M&E coordination experience in the Singapore construction industry</li><li>Able to work independently with strong problem-solving and communication skills</li><li>Familiar with local codes, practices, and authority submission procedures is a plus</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#77897 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
